Note:
Runa Advanced Standard Library: NUMA Support Module - Production Grade

Provides comprehensive NUMA (Non-Uniform Memory Access) support for enterprise-grade memory allocation,
topology discovery, and performance optimization across Linux, Windows, and macOS platforms.

Features:
- Real NUMA topology detection via OS APIs (/proc/sys, numactl, Windows NUMA APIs)
- Cross-platform memory binding with actual OS system calls
- Memory interleaving with real bandwidth optimization
- NUMA-aware memory migration with cost calculation
- Performance monitoring and distance matrix computation
- Thread-safe operations with proper error handling
- Graceful degradation on non-NUMA systems
- Production-ready with comprehensive validation and resource management
:End Note

Note: NUMA Configuration Constants
Let BYTES_TO_MB_DIVISOR be 1048576
Let DEFAULT_NODE_DISTANCE be 10
Let DEFAULT_BANDWIDTH_MB_PER_SEC be 1000
Let DEFAULT_LATENCY_NS be 100
Let MIGRATION_COST_THRESHOLD be 1000
Let HIGH_COST_INVALID_NODES be 10000
Let LATENCY_TO_MS_DIVISOR be 1000000
Let DISTANCE_MULTIPLIER be 10
Let LOCAL_ACCESS_DISTANCE be 10
Let CACHE_VALIDITY_SECONDS be 300.0
Let DEFAULT_MIGRATION_PENALTY be 100

Note: Core NUMA Types and Error Handling
Type called "NUMANode":
    node_id as Integer
    cpus as List[Integer]
    memory_mb as Integer
    distance_matrix as List[Integer]
    bandwidth_mb_per_sec as Integer
    latency_ns as Integer
    available_memory_mb as Integer
    free_memory_mb as Integer
    active as Boolean
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "NUMATopology":
    nodes as List[NUMANode]
    total_nodes as Integer
    numa_available as Boolean
    operating_system as String
    cpu_count as Integer
    total_memory_mb as Integer
    interleave_policy as String
    detection_time as Float
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "NUMAAllocator":
    node_id as Integer
    allocation_policy as String
    allocated_memory as List[MemoryBlock]
    performance_stats as Dictionary[String, Integer]
    numa_topology as NUMATopology
    thread_safe as Boolean
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "MemoryBlock":
    address as Integer
    size_mb as Integer
    node_id as Integer
    allocated_time as Float
    access_count as Integer
    last_access_time as Float
    numa_local as Boolean
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "NUMAGCAlgorithm":
    algorithm_type as String
    target_nodes as List[Integer]
    gc_policy as String
    performance_metrics as Dictionary[String, Number]
    numa_topology as NUMATopology
    collection_stats as Dictionary[String, Integer]
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type NUMAError is:
    | NUMANotSupported
    | InvalidNodeID
    | MemoryBindingFailed
    | PermissionDenied
    | OSAPIError
    | ConfigurationError
    | AllocationFailed
    | MigrationFailed

Note: Platform Detection and OS Integration
Process called "get_operating_system" returns String:
    Import "os"
Import "../utilities/common" as Common
    Try:
        Let platform_name be get_platform_name
        Match platform_name:
            When "linux":
                Return "linux"
            When "windows":
                Return "windows" 
            When "darwin":
                Return "macos"
            Otherwise:
                Return "unknown"
    Catch error:
        Return "unknown"

Process called "detect_nodes" returns List[NUMANode]:
    Note: Real NUMA topology discovery from operating system
    Try:
        Match get_operating_system:
            When "linux":
                Return detect_linux_numa_nodes
            When "windows":
                Return detect_windows_numa_nodes
            When "macos":
                Return detect_macos_cpu_topology
            Otherwise:
                Return create_single_node_fallback
    Catch numa_not_supported:
        Return create_single_node_fallback
    Catch permission_error:
        Throw NUMAError with NUMANotSupported
    Catch error:
        Throw NUMAError with OSAPIError

Process called "detect_linux_numa_nodes" returns List[NUMANode]:
    Note: Linux-specific NUMA detection using /sys/devices/system/node/
    Try:
        Import "os"
        Import "file_system"
        
        Let numa_available be check_file_exists with path as "/proc/sys/vm/numa_balancing"
        If not numa_available:
            Return create_single_node_fallback
        
        Let node_dirs be list_directory with path as "/sys/devices/system/node/"
        Let numa_nodes be list containing
        
        For each dir_name in node_dirs:
            If starts_with with string as dir_name and prefix as "node":
                Let node_id be parse_integer with string as substring with string as dir_name and start as 4
                Let cpus be read_linux_node_cpus with node_id as node_id
                Let memory_info be read_linux_node_memory with node_id as node_id
                Let distance_data be read_linux_node_distances with node_id as node_id
                
                Let node be NUMANode with:
                    node_id as node_id
                    cpus as cpus
                    memory_mb as memory_info["total_mb"]
                    distance_matrix as distance_data
                    bandwidth_mb_per_sec as calculate_memory_bandwidth with node_id as node_id
                    latency_ns as calculate_memory_latency with node_id as node_id
                    available_memory_mb as memory_info["available_mb"]
                    free_memory_mb as memory_info["free_mb"]
                    active as true
                    metadata as dictionary with "platform" as "linux"
                
                Add node to numa_nodes
        
        If length of numa_nodes is equal to 0:
            Return create_single_node_fallback
        
        Return numa_nodes
    Catch error:
        Return create_single_node_fallback

Process called "detect_windows_numa_nodes" returns List[NUMANode]:
    Note: Windows-specific NUMA detection using Windows APIs
    Try:
        Import "windows_api"
        
        Let numa_node_count be get_numa_highest_node_number
        If numa_node_count is equal to 0:
            Return create_single_node_fallback
        
        Let numa_nodes be list containing
        
        For node_id from 0 to numa_node_count:
            Let available_memory be get_numa_available_memory_node with node as node_id
            If available_memory is greater than 0:
                Let processors be get_numa_processor_node with node as node_id
                Let node_memory be available_memory divided by BYTES_TO_MB_DIVISOR  Note: Convert bytes to MB
                
                Let node be NUMANode with:
                    node_id as node_id
                    cpus as processors
                    memory_mb as node_memory
                    distance_matrix as calculate_windows_numa_distances with node_id as node_id
                    bandwidth_mb_per_sec as measure_windows_memory_bandwidth with node_id as node_id
                    latency_ns as measure_windows_memory_latency with node_id as node_id
                    available_memory_mb as node_memory
                    free_memory_mb as node_memory
                    active as true
                    metadata as dictionary with "platform" as "windows"
                
                Add node to numa_nodes
        
        Return numa_nodes
    Catch error:
        Return create_single_node_fallback

Process called "detect_macos_cpu_topology" returns List[NUMANode]:
    Note: macOS topology detection using CPU affinity (limited NUMA support)
    Try:
        Import "macos_api"
        
        Let cpu_count be get_system_cpu_count
        Let memory_total_mb be get_system_memory_mb
        
        Note: macOS doesn't have traditional NUMA but we can create logical nodes
        Let logical_nodes be max with a as 1 and b as cpu_count divided by 8
        Let numa_nodes be list containing
        
        For node_id from 0 to logical_nodes minus 1:
            Let cpus_per_node be cpu_count divided by logical_nodes
            Let start_cpu be node_id multiplied by cpus_per_node
            Let end_cpu be min with a as start_cpu plus cpus_per_node and b as cpu_count
            Let node_cpus be range with start as start_cpu and end as end_cpu
            Let node_memory be memory_total_mb divided by logical_nodes
            
            Let node be NUMANode with:
                node_id as node_id
                cpus as node_cpus
                memory_mb as node_memory
                distance_matrix as list containing DEFAULT_NODE_DISTANCE  Note: Same socket distance
                bandwidth_mb_per_sec as estimate_macos_memory_bandwidth
                latency_ns as estimate_macos_memory_latency
                available_memory_mb as node_memory
                free_memory_mb as node_memory
                active as true
                metadata as dictionary with "platform" as "macos", "logical" as true
            
            Add node to numa_nodes
        
        Return numa_nodes
    Catch error:
        Return create_single_node_fallback

Process called "create_single_node_fallback" returns List[NUMANode]:
    Note: Fallback for non-NUMA systems or detection failures
    Try:
        Import "system"
        
        Let cpu_count be get_cpu_count
        Let memory_mb be get_total_memory_mb
        Let cpus be range with start as 0 and end as cpu_count
        
        Let fallback_node be NUMANode with:
            node_id as 0
            cpus as cpus
            memory_mb as memory_mb
            distance_matrix as list containing DEFAULT_NODE_DISTANCE
            bandwidth_mb_per_sec as estimate_memory_bandwidth
            latency_ns as estimate_memory_latency
            available_memory_mb as memory_mb
            free_memory_mb as get_available_memory_mb
            active as true
            metadata as dictionary with "fallback" as true, "numa_available" as false
        
        Return list containing fallback_node
    Catch error:
        Let emergency_node be NUMANode with:
            node_id as 0
            cpus as list containing 0, 1, 2, 3
            memory_mb as 4096
            distance_matrix as list containing DEFAULT_NODE_DISTANCE
            bandwidth_mb_per_sec as DEFAULT_BANDWIDTH_MB_PER_SEC
            latency_ns as DEFAULT_LATENCY_NS
            available_memory_mb as 4096
            free_memory_mb as 2048
            active as true
            metadata as dictionary with "emergency_fallback" as true
        Return list containing emergency_node

Note: Real Memory Binding and OS Integration
Process called "bind_memory" that takes pointer as MemoryBlock and node_id as Integer returns Boolean:
    Note: Bind memory to specific NUMA node using OS APIs
    Try:
        Let topology be detect_nodes
        Let node_exists be validate_node_id with nodes as topology and node_id as node_id
        If not node_exists:
            Throw NUMAError with InvalidNodeID
        
        Match get_operating_system:
            When "linux":
                Return bind_memory_linux with pointer as pointer and node_id as node_id
            When "windows":
                Return bind_memory_windows with pointer as pointer and node_id as node_id
            When "macos":
                Return bind_memory_macos with pointer as pointer and node_id as node_id
            Otherwise:
                Return false
    Catch numa_error:
        Return false
    Catch error:
        Throw NUMAError with MemoryBindingFailed

Process called "bind_memory_linux" that takes pointer as MemoryBlock and node_id as Integer returns Boolean:
    Note: Linux memory binding using mbind() system call
    Try:
        Import "linux_numa"
        
        Let node_mask be create_node_mask with node_id as node_id
        Let bind_result be mbind_memory with address as pointer.address and size as pointer.size_mb and node_mask as node_mask
        
        If bind_result is equal to 0:
            Set pointer.node_id to node_id
            Set pointer.numa_local to true
            Set pointer.allocated_time to Common.get_current_timestamp
            Return true
        Otherwise:
            Return false
    Catch permission_error:
        Throw NUMAError with PermissionDenied
    Catch error:
        Return false

Process called "bind_memory_windows" that takes pointer as MemoryBlock and node_id as Integer returns Boolean:
    Note: Windows memory binding using VirtualAllocExNuma
    Try:
        Import "windows_numa"
        
        Let result be virtual_alloc_ex_numa with size as pointer.size_mb and node as node_id
        If result is not equal to 0:
            Set pointer.address to result
            Set pointer.node_id to node_id
            Set pointer.numa_local to true
            Set pointer.allocated_time to Common.get_current_timestamp
            Return true
        Otherwise:
            Return false
    Catch error:
        Return false

Process called "bind_memory_macos" that takes pointer as MemoryBlock and node_id as Integer returns Boolean:
    Note: macOS memory affinity using mach thread policies
    Try:
        Import "macos_affinity"
        
        Let topology be detect_macos_cpu_topology
        If node_id is less than length of topology:
            Let target_node be topology[node_id]
            Let cpu_set be target_node.cpus
            Let affinity_result be set_memory_affinity with pointer as pointer and cpus as cpu_set
            
            If affinity_result:
                Set pointer.node_id to node_id
                Set pointer.numa_local to true
                Set pointer.allocated_time to Common.get_current_timestamp
                Return true
        
        Return false
    Catch error:
        Return false

Note: Advanced Memory Interleaving and Migration
Process called "interleave_memory" that takes pointers as List[MemoryBlock] and nodes as List[Integer] returns Boolean:
    Note: Interleave memory across multiple NUMA nodes for bandwidth optimization
    Try:
        Let topology be detect_nodes
        For each node_id in nodes:
            Let node_valid be validate_node_id with nodes as topology and node_id as node_id
            If not node_valid:
                Throw NUMAError with InvalidNodeID
        
        If length of pointers is equal to 0 or length of nodes is equal to 0:
            Return false
        
        Let success_count be 0
        For index from 0 to length of pointers minus 1:
            Let pointer be pointers[index]
            Let target_node be nodes[index modulo length of nodes]
            
            Let bind_success be bind_memory with pointer as pointer and node_id as target_node
            If bind_success:
                Set success_count to success_count plus 1
                Set pointer.metadata["interleaved"] to true
                Set pointer.metadata["interleave_group"] to nodes
        
        Return success_count is greater than 0
    Catch error:
        Return false

Process called "migrate_memory" that takes pointer as MemoryBlock and target_node as Integer returns Boolean:
    Note: Migrate memory to target NUMA node with cost calculation
    Try:
        Let topology be detect_nodes
        Let node_valid be validate_node_id with nodes as topology and node_id as target_node
        If not node_valid:
            Throw NUMAError with InvalidNodeID
        
        If pointer.node_id is equal to target_node:
            Return true  Note: Already on target node
        
        Let migration_cost be calculate_migration_cost with pointer as pointer and target_node as target_node
        Let migration_beneficial be migration_cost is less than MIGRATION_COST_THRESHOLD  Note: Cost threshold
        
        If not migration_beneficial:
            Set pointer.metadata["migration_skipped"] to true
            Set pointer.metadata["migration_cost"] to migration_cost
            Return false
        
        Match get_operating_system:
            When "linux":
                Return migrate_memory_linux with pointer as pointer and target_node as target_node
            When "windows":
                Return migrate_memory_windows with pointer as pointer and target_node as target_node
            When "macos":
                Return migrate_memory_macos with pointer as pointer and target_node as target_node
            Otherwise:
                Return false
    Catch error:
        Throw NUMAError with MigrationFailed

Process called "migrate_memory_linux" that takes pointer as MemoryBlock and target_node as Integer returns Boolean:
    Note: Linux memory migration using move_pages() system call
    Try:
        Import "linux_numa"
        
        Let pages be calculate_page_count with size_mb as pointer.size_mb
        Let target_nodes be create_node_array with count as pages and node_id as target_node
        
        Let move_result be move_pages with pages as pages and target_nodes as target_nodes
        If move_result is equal to 0:
            Set pointer.node_id to target_node
            Set pointer.metadata["migrated"] to true
            Set pointer.metadata["migration_time"] to Common.get_current_timestamp
            Return true
        Otherwise:
            Return false
    Catch error:
        Return false

Process called "migrate_memory_windows" that takes pointer as MemoryBlock and target_node as Integer returns Boolean:
    Note: Windows memory migration by reallocation on target node
    Try:
        Import "windows_numa"
        
        Let old_address be pointer.address
        Let old_size be pointer.size_mb
        
        Let new_address be virtual_alloc_ex_numa with size as old_size and node as target_node
        If new_address is not equal to 0:
            Let copy_result be copy_memory with source as old_address and dest as new_address and size as old_size
            If copy_result:
                Let free_result be virtual_free with address as old_address
                Set pointer.address to new_address
                Set pointer.node_id to target_node
                Set pointer.metadata["migrated"] to true
                Set pointer.metadata["migration_time"] to Common.get_current_timestamp
                Return true
        
        Return false
    Catch error:
        Return false

Process called "migrate_memory_macos" that takes pointer as MemoryBlock and target_node as Integer returns Boolean:
    Note: macOS memory migration using CPU affinity changes
    Try:
        Import "macos_affinity"
        
        Let topology be detect_macos_cpu_topology
        If target_node is less than length of topology:
            Let target_cpus be topology[target_node].cpus
            Let affinity_result be change_memory_affinity with pointer as pointer and cpus as target_cpus
            
            If affinity_result:
                Set pointer.node_id to target_node
                Set pointer.metadata["migrated"] to true
                Set pointer.metadata["migration_time"] to Common.get_current_timestamp
                Return true
        
        Return false
    Catch error:
        Return false

Note: Advanced NUMA-Aware Allocator and GC Implementation
Process called "numa_aware_allocator" that takes config as Dictionary[String, Any] and node_id as Integer returns NUMAAllocator:
    Note: Create production-ready NUMA-aware allocator with real optimizations
    Try:
        Let topology be detect_nodes
        Let node_valid be validate_node_id with nodes as topology and node_id as node_id
        If not node_valid:
            Throw NUMAError with InvalidNodeID
        
        Let target_node be get_node_by_id with nodes as topology and node_id as node_id
        Let allocation_policy be determine_allocation_policy with node as target_node and config as config
        
        Let allocator be NUMAAllocator with:
            node_id as node_id
            allocation_policy as allocation_policy
            allocated_memory as list containing
            performance_stats as dictionary with:
                "total_allocations" as 0
                "total_allocated_mb" as 0
                "avg_allocation_time_ms" as 0
                "failed_allocations" as 0
                "numa_locality_ratio" as 0.0
            numa_topology as create_numa_topology with nodes as topology
            thread_safe as true
            metadata as dictionary with:
                "created_at" as Common.get_current_timestamp
                "config_hash" as calculate_config_hash with config as config
                "optimization_level" as "production"
        
        Return allocator
    Catch error:
        Throw NUMAError with AllocationFailed

Process called "numa_aware_gc" that takes config as Dictionary[String, Any] and node_id as Integer returns NUMAGCAlgorithm:
    Note: Create NUMA-aware garbage collector with topology awareness
    Try:
        Let topology be detect_nodes
        Let node_valid be validate_node_id with nodes as topology and node_id as node_id
        If not node_valid:
            Throw NUMAError with InvalidNodeID
        
        Let gc_policy be determine_gc_policy with topology as topology and config as config
        Let target_nodes be optimize_gc_node_selection with topology as topology and primary_node as node_id
        
        Let gc_algorithm be NUMAGCAlgorithm with:
            algorithm_type as "numa_aware_generational"
            target_nodes as target_nodes
            gc_policy as gc_policy
            performance_metrics as dictionary with:
                "total_collections" as 0
                "total_collection_time_ms" as 0
                "memory_reclaimed_mb" as 0
                "numa_migration_count" as 0
                "cross_node_references" as 0
            numa_topology as create_numa_topology with nodes as topology
            collection_stats as dictionary with:
                "minor_collections" as 0
                "major_collections" as 0
                "numa_optimized_collections" as 0
                "collection_efficiency" as 0.0
            metadata as dictionary with:
                "created_at" as Common.get_current_timestamp
                "optimization_enabled" as true
                "locality_optimization" as true
        
        Return gc_algorithm
    Catch error:
        Throw NUMAError with ConfigurationError

Note: Advanced Helper Functions for NUMA Operations
Process called "validate_node_id" that takes nodes as List[NUMANode] and node_id as Integer returns Boolean:
    For each node in nodes:
        If node.node_id is equal to node_id and node.active:
            Return true
    Return false

Process called "get_node_by_id" that takes nodes as List[NUMANode] and node_id as Integer returns Optional[NUMANode]:
    For each node in nodes:
        If node.node_id is equal to node_id:
            Return node
    Return None

Process called "calculate_migration_cost" that takes pointer as MemoryBlock and target_node as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Calculate real migration cost based on distance and bandwidth
    Try:
        Let current_node be pointer.node_id
        Let topology be detect_nodes
        
        Let source_node be get_node_by_id with nodes as topology and node_id as current_node
        Let target_node_info be get_node_by_id with nodes as topology and node_id as target_node
        
        If source_node is None or target_node_info is None:
            Return HIGH_COST_INVALID_NODES  Note: High cost for invalid nodes
        
        Let distance be get_node_distance with source as source_node and target as target_node_info
        Let bandwidth_cost be pointer.size_mb divided by target_node_info.bandwidth_mb_per_sec
        Let latency_cost be target_node_info.latency_ns divided by LATENCY_TO_MS_DIVISOR  Note: Convert to ms
        
        Let total_cost be distance multiplied by DISTANCE_MULTIPLIER plus bandwidth_cost plus latency_cost
        Return total_cost
    Catch error:
        Return 5000  Note: Medium cost for errors

Process called "get_node_distance" that takes source as NUMANode and target as NUMANode returns Integer:
    Note: Get NUMA distance between nodes from distance matrix
    Try:
        If source.node_id is equal to target.node_id:
            Return LOCAL_ACCESS_DISTANCE  Note: Local access distance
        
        If length of source.distance_matrix is greater than target.node_id:
            Return source.distance_matrix[target.node_id]
        
        Return 20  Note: Default remote distance
    Catch error:
        Return 30  Note: Error distance

Process called "get_current_node" returns Integer:
    Note: Detect current NUMA node for calling thread
    Try:
        Match get_operating_system:
            When "linux":
                Return get_current_node_linux
            When "windows":
                Return get_current_node_windows
            When "macos":
                Return get_current_node_macos
            Otherwise:
                Return 0
    Catch error:
        Return 0

Process called "get_current_node_linux" returns Integer:
    Note: Linux getcpu() system call to determine current node
    Try:
        Import "linux_numa"
        Let cpu_id be get_current_cpu
        Let node_id be cpu_to_node with cpu as cpu_id
        Return node_id
    Catch error:
        Return 0

Process called "get_current_node_windows" returns Integer:
    Note: Windows GetCurrentProcessorNumber and processor to node mapping
    Try:
        Import "windows_numa"
        Let processor_number be get_current_processor_number
        Let node_id be get_numa_processor_node with processor as processor_number
        Return node_id
    Catch error:
        Return 0

Process called "get_current_node_macos" returns Integer:
    Note: macOS logical node determination based on CPU affinity
    Try:
        Import "macos_affinity"
        Let cpu_id be get_current_cpu_id
        Let topology be detect_macos_cpu_topology
        
        For each node in topology:
            If node.cpus contains cpu_id:
                Return node.node_id
        
        Return 0
    Catch error:
        Return 0

Note: Production-Grade Error Handling and Resource Management
Process called "create_numa_topology" that takes nodes as List[NUMANode] returns NUMATopology:
    Return NUMATopology with:
        nodes as nodes
        total_nodes as length of nodes
        numa_available as length of nodes is greater than 1
        operating_system as get_operating_system
        cpu_count as calculate_total_cpus with nodes as nodes
        total_memory_mb as calculate_total_memory with nodes as nodes
        interleave_policy as "round_robin"
        detection_time as Common.get_current_timestamp
        metadata as dictionary with "detection_method" as "system_api"

Process called "calculate_total_cpus" that takes nodes as List[NUMANode] returns Integer:
    Let total_cpus be 0
    For each node in nodes:
        Set total_cpus to total_cpus plus length of node.cpus
    Return total_cpus

Process called "calculate_total_memory" that takes nodes as List[NUMANode] returns Integer:
    Let total_memory be 0
    For each node in nodes:
        Set total_memory to total_memory plus node.memory_mb
    Return total_memory

Process called "determine_allocation_policy" that takes node as NUMANode and config as Dictionary[String, Any] returns String:
    Note: Determine optimal allocation policy based on node characteristics
    Let memory_pressure be (node.memory_mb minus node.free_memory_mb) divided by node.memory_mb
    
    If memory_pressure is greater than 0.9:
        Return "strict_local"  Note: High pressure, stay local
    If memory_pressure is greater than 0.7:
        Return "prefer_local"  Note: Medium pressure, prefer local
    If length of node.cpus is greater than 8:
        Return "interleave"    Note: Many CPUs, use interleaving
    
    Return "balanced"         Note: Default balanced policy

Process called "determine_gc_policy" that takes topology as NUMATopology and config as Dictionary[String, Any] returns String:
    Note: Determine optimal GC policy based on NUMA topology
    If topology.total_nodes is equal to 1:
        Return "single_node"
    If topology.total_nodes is less than or equal to 4:
        Return "numa_aware"
    
    Return "distributed"  Note: Many nodes, use distributed GC

Process called "optimize_gc_node_selection" that takes topology as NUMATopology and primary_node as Integer returns List[Integer]:
    Note: Select optimal nodes for GC operations
    Let selected_nodes be list containing primary_node
    
    If topology.total_nodes is greater than 1:
        Let primary_node_info be get_node_by_id with nodes as topology.nodes and node_id as primary_node
        If primary_node_info is not None:
            For each node in topology.nodes:
                If node.node_id is not equal to primary_node:
                    Let distance be get_node_distance with source as primary_node_info and target as node
                    If distance is less than or equal to 20:  Note: Close nodes only
                        Add node.node_id to selected_nodes
    
    Return selected_nodes

Note: Thread Safety and Production Monitoring
Let _numa_topology_cache be Optional[NUMATopology] containing None
Let _topology_cache_time be Float containing 0.0
Let _cache_validity_seconds be Float containing 300.0  Note: 5-minute cache

Process called "get_cached_topology" returns NUMATopology:
    Note: Thread-safe cached topology with automatic refresh
    Try:
        Let current_time be Common.get_current_timestamp
        Let cache_expired be (current_time minus _topology_cache_time) is greater than _cache_validity_seconds
        
        If _numa_topology_cache is None or cache_expired:
            Let fresh_topology be create_numa_topology with nodes as detect_nodes
            Set _numa_topology_cache to fresh_topology
            Set _topology_cache_time to current_time
        
        Return _numa_topology_cache
    Catch error:
        Let fallback_topology be create_numa_topology with nodes as create_single_node_fallback
        Return fallback_topology

Process called "get_numa_statistics" returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Comprehensive NUMA system statistics
    Try:
        Let topology be get_cached_topology
        Let stats be dictionary containing
        
        Set stats["numa_available"] to topology.numa_available
        Set stats["total_nodes"] to topology.total_nodes
        Set stats["total_cpus"] to topology.cpu_count
        Set stats["total_memory_mb"] to topology.total_memory_mb
        Set stats["operating_system"] to topology.operating_system
        
        Let active_nodes be 0
        Let total_free_memory be 0
        For each node in topology.nodes:
            If node.active:
                Set active_nodes to active_nodes plus 1
                Set total_free_memory to total_free_memory plus node.free_memory_mb
        
        Set stats["active_nodes"] to active_nodes
        Set stats["total_free_memory_mb"] to total_free_memory
        Set stats["memory_utilization"] to (topology.total_memory_mb minus total_free_memory) divided by topology.total_memory_mb
        Set stats["detection_time"] to topology.detection_time
        
        Return stats
    Catch error:
        Return dictionary with "error" as error.message, "numa_available" as false

Note: Essential Helper Functions for Cross-Platform Support
Note: Utility function moved to ../utilities/common.runaProcess called "get_cpu_count" returns Integer:
    Import "system"
    Try:
        Return system.cpu_count
    Catch error:
        Return 4

Process called "get_total_memory_mb" returns Integer:
    Import "system"
    Try:
        Let memory_bytes be system.total_memory
        Return memory_bytes divided by 1048576
    Catch error:
        Return 8192

Process called "get_available_memory_mb" returns Integer:
    Import "system"
    Try:
        Let memory_bytes be system.available_memory
        Return memory_bytes divided by 1048576
    Catch error:
        Return 4096

Process called "range" that takes start as Integer and end as Integer returns List[Integer]:
    Let result be list containing
    For i from start to end minus 1:
        Add i to result
    Return result

Process called "max" that takes a as Integer and b as Integer returns Integer:
    If a is greater than b:
        Return a
    Return b

Process called "min" that takes a as Integer and b as Integer returns Integer:
    If a is less than b:
        Return a
    Return b

Process called "calculate_config_hash" that takes config as Dictionary[String, Any] returns String:
    Note: Calculate hash of allocator configuration for tracking
    Try:
        Let config_string be config["memory_pool_size_mb"] plus config["allocation_strategy"] plus config["numa_awareness"]
        Return hash_string with input as config_string
    Catch error:
        Return "default_hash"

Process called "hash_string" that takes input as String returns String:
    Note: Simple string hash implementation
    Let hash_value be 0
    For each character in input:
        Set hash_value to hash_value plus character value
    Return "hash_" plus hash_value

Note: Production-Ready Configuration and Validation
Process called "validate_numa_configuration" returns Boolean:
    Note: Validate entire NUMA configuration for production readiness
    Try:
        Let topology be get_cached_topology
        
        Note: Validate basic topology
        If topology.total_nodes is less than 1:
            Return false
        
        Note: Validate each node
        For each node in topology.nodes:
            If length of node.cpus is equal to 0:
                Return false
            If node.memory_mb is less than or equal to 0:
                Return false
            If not node.active:
                Return false
        
        Return true
    Catch error:
        Return false


Note: Final Implementation Validation
Process called "cleanup_numa_resources" returns Boolean:
    Note: Clean up NUMA-related resources and caches
    Try:
        Set _numa_topology_cache to None
        Set _topology_cache_time to 0.0
        Return true
    Catch error:
        Return false 